description.et:
Active participation in the respective lecture/seminar: 40% of the final grade. Active participation is considered when a student presents a preselected topic in the classroom.

Grading of the participation:
E - 51-60 points; the coverage of the subject is poor but sufficient to cover the basics;
D - 61-70 points; the coverage of the subject is logical and associated but lacking in detail;
C - 71-80 points; the coverage of the subject is good but the student has not managed to cover all of the topics angles and relevant points in a sufficient depth;
B - 81-90 points; the student has covered the subject very well, created associations between different concepts and built a clear thorough understanding of the subject as a whole. The answers have sufficient detail;
A - 91-100 points; the student has excellent knowledge of the topic. The presentation provides complete overview of what has been asked from the student and clearly indicate that the student has covered all of the materials in sufficient depth.

Written paper (60% of the final grade) about the topic presented during the seminars:

Graded components of the essay:
- Compliance with the provided task; 
- The level of knowledge in the field relevant to the essay, including the broader knowledge about the developments in the relevant field; 
- Logical structure and cogency of the argumentation; 
- Level of analysis present in the paper.  

Grading of the essay: 
E - 51-60 points; the coverage of the subject is poor but sufficient to cover the basics;
D - 61-70 points; the coverage of the subject is logical and associated but lacking in detail;
C - 71-80 points; the coverage of the subject is good but the student has not managed to cover all of the topics angles and relevant points in a sufficient depth;
B - 81-90 points; the student has covered the subject very well, created associations between different concepts and built a clear thorough understanding of the subject as a whole. The answers have sufficient detail;
A - 91-100 points; the student has excellent knowledge of the topic. The answers provide complete overview of what has been asked from the student and clearly indicate that the student has covered all of the materials in sufficient depth.
